rows.label: qst001001_msg0001
rows.name:
I can't leave my post, but I've
got to do something...

rows.label: qst001001_msg0002
rows.name:
Ahh, well, the thing is, we've got
ourselves a little problem here.

rows.label: qst001001_msg0003
rows.name:
The kids went out to play, but it's been
ages and they haven't come back.

rows.label: qst001001_msg0004
rows.name:
When they go out to play, sometimes
they come back with stuff we need,
like food or raw materials.

rows.label: qst001001_msg0005
rows.name:
It's all well and good but I worry. I've
asked them to stop, but you know kids.

rows.label: qst001001_msg0006
rows.name:
They just want to help the village
in their own way, I suppose.
Playing at mercs.

rows.label: qst001001_msg0007
rows.name:
At any rate, it's not unusual
for them to be late back, but...

rows.label: qst001001_msg0008
rows.name:
Whichever way you slice it, they've
been gone an awfully long time.

rows.label: qst001001_msg0009
rows.name:
I don't want to overly worry,
but you do hear stories...

rows.label: qst001001_msg0010
rows.name:
I want to go make sure they'reokay,
but I can't abandon my duties.

rows.label: qst001001_msg0011
rows.name:
You'll go and check for me?
Thanks, that would be a huge help!

rows.label: qst001001_msg0012
rows.name:
The kids said they were heading over
Greatmaw Rapids way.

rows.label: qst001001_msg0013
rows.name:
I'd start looking there.
Thanks a lot!

rows.label: qst001001_msg0101
rows.name:
The kids are probably over by
the Greatmaw Rapids.
